sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious downloader and stager, likely a variant of a custom backdoor or loader. It exhibits several high-confidence indicators of malicious intent: it hides its console window immediately upon execution, implements persistence by creating a registry entry named 'MyDownloader' under HKCU, and employs a timing-based anti-analysis check (using Sleep and GetTickCount64) to detect sandboxes. The core functionality involves using the WinHTTP library to download an encrypted payload (referenced by the string '/teste.bin'), decrypting it via a simple XOR cipher (key 0x5a), and executing it in memory by allocating RWX space with VirtualAlloc and spawning a new thread. The PDB path '%USERPROFILE%\Music\stux2\x64\Release\stux2.pdb' is a notable IOC.
